<glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>multiple myeloma</term> <meaning>a blood cancer affecting plasma cells that are found in the bone marrow; abnormal plasma cells multiply rapidly, crowd out normal blood-producing cells, and produce an abnormal protein that leaves the bone marrow and damages organs in the body</meaning></definition>
